<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF208-285-781  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 285 781.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Software  Sept 1989 v6 n5 p80(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Document standard focuses on the larger picture. (NASA's SoftwareManagement and Assurance Program standards) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tice, George.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The new version 4.3 of the National Aeronautics and SpaceAdministration's (NASA's) standards for information-systemlife-cycle and documentation management, the Software Managementand Assurance Program (SMAP), provides standards for tailoringdocumentation to the size and complexity of a softwareapplication.andP;  SMAP 4.3 provides guidance for document developmentin the planning, engineering, assurance, and tracking aspects ofapplications programming.andP;  The standard specifically facilitatesinformation access, communications, life-cycle process definition,project management, documentation generation (including thedynamics between documents and tailoring to project requirements)and assurance activities for a wide range of project sizes andtypes.andP;  SMAP is available from the University of Georgia's Cosmicprogram for $100.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Product:   NASA Software Management and Assurance Program (standards).andO;Topic:     StandardsSoftware PackagesDocument PreparationNASAApplications ProgrammingDocumentation.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Example product-specification document. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>